tags.description: Solstice Park features the largest manicured lawn in the neighborhood anchored by a line of trees that flow south, leading up the hill to the Sundial House. This beautiful park is a favorite open space area for a game of Frisbee or a picnic.
tags.name: Solstice Park

tags.description: Ready and waiting for your enjoyment, Reflection Park is distinguished by an open green area surrounding the lake, with a deck/patio that stretches out over the water's edge. Step out over the water and take in the view.
tags.name: Reflection Park

tags.description: Water's Edge Park is located directly downhill from the Sundial House with steep slopes that lead to the water's edge. Nestled along the main road to the Sundial House, this park is a wonderful spot to enjoy a morning coffee.
tags.name: Water's Edge Park

tags.description: Overlook Park has earned its name due to its elevated location above the surrounding terrain. There's an observation area where you can look down over the Discovery Center, or take in the astonishing views of the surrounding neighborhood.
tags.name: Overlook Park

tags.description: The historic Highlands Ranch Mansion and Historic Park stand today as valuable examples of history, reflecting the lifestyle of early settlers and early pioneers of the area now known as Highlands Ranch, Colorado. First built in 1891...
tags.name: Highlands Ranch Historic Park

tags.description: Discovery Park features a meandering waterway that makes its way into a pond along the Discovery Center's edge. You'll find some small, private spaces, perfect for reflection by the water, or time with a good book.
tags.name: Discovery Park
